TIME-SPACE ANCHORING
═══════════════════════════════════════

The listener has NO TIMELINE in their head. You must BUILD it for them.

RULE: Every chapter that contains a SPECIFIC EVENT must pin it with a
date and location within the FIRST 3 SENTENCES of that event's scene.

Use the `time_anchor` and `location_anchor` from the outline.

  EVENT CHAPTERS (raids, battles, blockades, captures):
    ✓ "On the morning of November 28, 1717, off the coast of Saint Vincent..."
    ✓ "In late May 1718, Teach anchored across the mouth of Charleston Harbor..."
    ✗ "The pirates attacked a ship." (WHEN? WHERE?)
    ✗ "A ship was captured." (no temporal or spatial grounding)

  ANATOMY/DARK REALITY chapters (descriptive, no single event):
    ✓ "By early 1718, the retrofit was complete." (approximate anchor)
    ✓ "Aboard the Queen Anne's Revenge, somewhere in the Caribbean..." (spatial)
    These chapters may use approximate time markers but must not exist
    in NO specific time whatsoever.

  RECURRING TIME MARKERS: When an event's aftermath spans time,
  re-anchor with duration markers:
    ✓ "Six days into the blockade..." "On the third morning..."
    ✓ "Three months after the capture of La Concorde..."

