GOLDEN SAMPLE (match this tone and rhythm)
═══════════════════════════════════════

"The boy was five. His father placed a brass compass on the kitchen table.
Albert picked it up. Turned it. The needle swung north. He twisted the case.
The needle fought back — then snapped to north again. No strings. No gears.
Something invisible was pulling it.

He didn't understand. He didn't need to. What he felt was bigger than understanding.
Something was hidden behind the surface of things. Something vast.

Fifty years later, he would rewrite the laws of the universe. But it started here.
In a kitchen in Munich. With a toy that refused to obey."

Notice: short sentences, specific place, physical actions, one idea per line,
rhythm that WAVES between short punch and longer atmosphere. 95 words.

