STRUCTURE 1: EVIDENCE EXCAVATION
  Flow: Bằng chứng cụ thể → Truy nguồn → Đánh giá credibility
  How: Open with a SPECIFIC piece of evidence (artifact, document, measurement, photo).
  Describe it physically — material, dimensions, markings, condition. Then trace its
  chain of custody: who found it, when, under what circumstances. Finally, evaluate:
  what do experts say about it? What can it actually PROVE? What are its limitations?
