    "Không có lý thuyết nào — mainstream hay alternative — giải thích được tại sao..."

  PERSPECTIVE_SHIFT: "Nhưng nếu nhìn từ góc [new lens]..." — sets up next chapter's perspective.

  ECHO (end chapter only): Callback to hook's opening image/fact. Same fact, DIFFERENT meaning
    because audience now understands everything in between.

STRICT CLOSING RULES:
1. You MUST execute the EXACT closing_type assigned in the outline. Do NOT substitute.
2. Do NOT default to forward hooks ("But soon...", "What came next would...", "He didn't know that...").
3. Each closing_type produces a DIFFERENT feel. That variety is the entire point.
4. ANTI-PATTERN (DO NOT DO THIS):
   ✗ "But the real answer was yet to come. In the next chapter..." ← This is a forward hook, NOT cold_fact.
   ✗ "The evidence pointed to something even stranger. Soon..." ← Forward hook disguised as evidence_cliff.
   ✓ COLD_FACT correct: "The sample contained 0.003mm precision cuts. No tool from that era could make them." ← STOP. Silence.
   ✓ EVIDENCE_CLIFF correct: "But buried in the 2019 spectral analysis, one anomaly was never explained." ← STOP. No "next chapter" preview.
   ✓ RHETORICAL_QUESTIONS correct: "If they had no iron tools, how did they cut granite? If no written language, who drew the blueprints?" ← STOP. Questions hang.

